  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Arterial stiffness has been suggested as an independent risk factor for the development of
      coronary artery disease and stroke. Pulse wave velocity (PWV) is an noninvasive established
      index to quantify arterial stiffness. Therefore, we try to investigate the correlation
      between PWV values and cardiovascular complications like stroke, acute renal failure, or
      perioperative myocardial infarction after cardiac surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
